This paper is primarily focused on visual recognition and pattern mining using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their filters, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the efficiency of their approach, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
